      <h1 class='title'>No application after formation of subsequent civil partnership or marriage</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='grand-committee-report-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 cc312-3GC</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_312gc' title='Col. 312GC &mdash; HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c312GC' name='column_312gc' href='#column_312gc' rel='bookmark'>312GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-03996'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_607' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        3 (1) If&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) the civil partnership has been dissolved or annulled, and</li>
        <li>(b) after the dissolution or annulment, one of the civil partners forms a subsequent civil partnership or marriage,</li></ol>
        
        <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_313gc' title='Col. 313GC &mdash; HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c313GC' name='column_313gc' href='#column_313gc' rel='bookmark'>313GC</a>
        that civil partner shall not be entitled to make, in relation to the civil partnership, an application for an order under paragraph 9 Or 13.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-03997'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_608' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (2) The reference in sub-paragraph (1) to the forming of a subsequent civil partnership or marriage includes a reference to the forming of a civil partnership or marriage which is by law void or voidable.
      </p>
      <ol class='xoxo'>
        
      </ol>
      
